<title>ECUADOR: Ecuador's Bucaram to reverse rate rises - official.</title>
<headline>Ecuador's Bucaram to reverse rate rises - official.</headline>
<dateline>QUITO, Ecuador 1997-02-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ecuador's President Abdala Bucaram has decided to suspend big price increases for gas and electricity which have sparked social unrest and to freeze fuel prices, a top official said on Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;He is preparing to announce in the next few minutes the suspension of the economic measures related to the price of gas, electricity tariffs and a price freeze for fuels,&quot; Communication Secretary Mariana Ordunez said.  </p>
<p>The price rises in January triggered unrest which culminated in a general strike which began Wednesday. Unions Thursday said they would stay on strike until Bucaram was ousted.</p>
<p>Congress was due to meet for an extraordinary session at 6 p.m. (2300 GMT) amid speculation that legislators might try to dismiss the president.</p>
